For Ed Yong, a science writer at the Atlantic, the big question about this is: What will “normal” look like?
On Thursday’s episode of What Next, I spoke with Yong about what our new normal will look like.
Ed Yong: I think it will require the vast majority of people to be immune to the virus in some way.
There was a fund that was meant to prepare the country and its public health infrastructure specifically for this.
The CDC has long been viewed as one of the greatest public health agencies in the world, if not the greatest.